Classes in jbt.execution.context that implement IContext
 class BasicContext
          Basic implementation of the IContext interface.
 class HierarchicalContext
          A HierarchicalContext is a context that stores a parent IContext to fall back to when it cannot find a particular variable in its own set of variables.
 class SafeContext
          The SafeContext represents a context that can be used to safely controls modifications in another context (the input context).
 class SafeOutputContext
          The SafeOutputContext represents a context that can be used to safely controls modifications in another context (the input context).
